---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof for Painters — Reviews That Win More Painting Jobs | SocialProof" description="Painters and painting contractors: homeowners choose on trust and quality. SocialProof helps you collect and display customer testimonials that turn prospects into booked jobs.">
  <main>
    <section style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.5rem;">
      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Social Proof for Painters
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Painting is visual — but most customers can't see your work until they've already hired you. That's where testimonials do the work: real words from real homeowners describing the quality, the cleanup, the process. SocialProof helps you collect those stories and display them where new customers decide.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Why testimonials matter for painters</h2>
      <p>A homeowner getting multiple quotes will often choose based on "who seems most professional" — and that judgment is made almost entirely from your website and visible track record. A portfolio helps, but testimonials are what make people trust the portfolio is real.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem;">SocialProof makes it easy to collect testimonials right after job completion (when clients are most delighted) and display them automatically on your website — no tech skills required.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">What converts in painter testimonials</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Prep and cleanup:</strong> "They covered everything, taped perfectly, and left the house cleaner than they found it."</li>
        <li><strong>Color matching:</strong> "Matched the exact color we wanted and touched up a few spots we hadn't even noticed."</li>
        <li><strong>Reliability:</strong> "Showed up exactly when they said, finished exactly on schedule."</li>
        <li><strong>Transformation:</strong> "The whole house feels brand new. Worth every penny."</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">How it works</h2>
      <ol style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li>After the final walkthrough, send your customer a SocialProof link via text</li>
        <li>They submit a quick testimonial — no app, no account needed</li>
        <li>You approve it and it appears on your website instantly</li>
        <li>Every new estimate request comes from someone who's already read what your customers say</li>
      </ol>

      <div style="background:#f8f9fa;border-radius:12px;padding:2rem;margin-top:2.5rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Free forever for 1 active widget</h3>
        <p style="color:#555;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Start collecting and displaying testimonials today. No credit card required.</p>
        <a href="https://socialproof.dev/signup" style="display:inline-block;background:#0070f3;color:#fff;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:8px;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;">Start free</a>
      </div>

      <section style="margin-top:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.4rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Frequently asked questions</h2>

        <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
          "@context": "https://schema.org",
          "@type": "FAQPage",
          "mainEntity": [
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "How do I get testimonials from painting customers?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Ask right after the final walkthrough — that's when satisfaction is highest. SocialProof gives you a simple share link to text or email. Customers click it and submit a testimonial in under two minutes, no account needed."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "Should I show before and after photos with testimonials?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Yes, photos dramatically increase trust for visual services like painting. SocialProof supports photo submissions alongside testimonials, so customers can share images of the finished work."
              }
            }
          ]
        })}>
        </script>

        <details style="border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:8px;padding:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          <summary style="font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;">How do I get testimonials from painting customers?</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;color:#555;">Ask right after the final walkthrough — that's when satisfaction is highest. SocialProof gives you a simple link to text or email customers. They submit in under two minutes, no account needed.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:8px;padding:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          <summary style="font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;">Should I show before and after photos with testimonials?</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;color:#555;">Yes — photos dramatically increase trust for visual services. SocialProof supports photo submissions alongside testimonials so customers can share images of the finished work.</p>
        </details>
      </section>
    </section>
  </main>

<div class="footer-links" style="margin-top:2rem;padding-top:1.5rem;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:0.9rem;">
